I got stuck when I still had a few people and traits left, and no more clues. I had to look closely. It forced me to examine the constraints again and again, and I identified that the Artist and Sports must fit in Group 4.

At this point, I needed to check the assignment of jobs and hobbies and drinks.

I got stuck again and realized there may be a specific *order* to the assignments. When all of the constraints are used, and no more clues are left, the best and most likely pattern is that the assignment of attributes follows the listing of attributes in the puzzle.

When I started to organize the groups according to the "Attribute list," things began to click, revealing the complete picture. The puzzle’s solution became clear.
*   Iris: {Red, Hamster, Soda, Chef, Music}
*   Alice: {Yellow, Parrot, Smoothie, Nurse, Dancing}
